R: @aaltay @chamikaramj only adding Read transform in this PR, to keep it small. Write is coming next. Here is an example job for reference, https://pantheon.corp.google.com/dataflow/job/2016-11-21_11_55_02-8639619996891277831?project=deft-testing-integration2

R: @tgroh 

Here's a quick summary of the approach:

 - Expand stateful `ParDo.BoundMulti` into `GbkIntoKeyedWorkItems` followed by new pseudo-primitive `StatefulParDo`.
 - Add `StatefulParDoEvaluatorFactory`:
    - Here is where the cleanup scheduling is owned
    - Delegates everything else to `ParDoEvaluatorFactory` and `ParDoEvaluator`, involved some refactor to support.

I'll need to add more tests for `StatefuParDoEvaluatorFactory` to make sure that the normal processing aspects of it are not botched. It should be able to also pass all normal `ParDo` tests. It would be great to be able to re-use them by re-running `ParDoTest` with an over-zealous override that always used the stateful expansion.
+R: @tgroh
